  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Regulatory Measures\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Asset freezing and seizure\n- International information sharing\n\n4. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- License revocation for financial institutions\n- Personal liability for executives\n\n5. Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Central banks\n- Regulatory compliance departments\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial sectors.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
